  "prompt": "How much time does it take to get a marriage certificate in India?",
  "response": "Obtaining a marriage certificate in India typically involves several steps and can vary depending on the state and local authorities. Generally, the process can take anywhere from a few days to a few weeks. Here's a rough overview of the steps involved:\n\n1. **Application Submission**: The couple needs to submit an application form, along with the required documentation (proof of age, address, photographs, etc.) to the relevant marriage registrar.\n\n2. **Verification**: The submitted documents are verified by the authorities. This step can take a few days.\n\n3. **Notice Period** (in case of Special Marriage Act): If the marriage is being registered under the Special Marriage Act, there is a mandatory 30-day notice period during which the intention to marry is published publicly to allow for any objections.\n\n4. **Appointment Date**: After verification and notice period (if applicable), the couple is given an appointment date for the registration of the marriage and issuance of the certificate.\n\n5. **Registration Ceremony**: On the appointed date, the couple needs to be present along with witnesses. The marriage certificate is issued after the registration is done.\n\nIn summary, the time frame can vary based on the method of registration (Hindu Marriage Act vs. Special Marriage Act) and local administrative efficiency, but generally it can take anywhere from a few days to about a month.",
